N>Laurenia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/18/01 8:49:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need help for a Battle ROYAL</span><hr size=1> I may not be that experienced in Battle royals, but heres my opinion: the mage will only have a couple of buffs to bring up, while the druids and shammy all have a large amount, especially the druids. so i figure he will have a lot of his mana left when battle starts. so dont buff urself too much unless the mage is preoccupied, because he can concentrate on 2 peeps with pet <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><IMG SRC = "http://laurenia.homestead.com/files/laurenia_sig_final.jpg" WIDTH=383 HEIGHT=223  BORDER=0></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=leadar>Leadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/18/01 12:21:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Pvp</span><hr size=1> First, you need to make sure that FEAR is NOT allowed by the necros, or none of you will stand a chance (other than the necros).  If necros are allowed to fear, you ALL need to kill them first, or you are dead.  <br><br>If fear is not allowed, then you need to conserve your mana and try to stay alive till the end.  Melee, and pet classes have an advantage in a free for all, because casters will run oom, and wont be able to finish anyone off at the end, where melees and pet classes will be able to finish people off with their pets and melee abilities.  <br><br>Id play the coward and hide in a fire pot until near the end, try not to attract too much attention to yourself, keep your finger on the heal button to heal yourself, then I'd jump out and finish off whoever is still standing, hehe.  <br><br>People that should be killed first (in order for things to go well for you in the end), warrior, necros, mage, shammy.   Tough call, but my money would be on one of those classes to be the last standing in the format you are describing, because everyone will run oom eventually, and it will come down to who is able to kill without mana. <br><br>Spyder <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=duffmiver>dUFFmIVER</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/3/02 10:14:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> fOR CLASSES THAT ARE SOMEWHAT RELIANT ON BUFFS-TWO WORDS</span><hr size=1> pUMICE sTONE<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udamudgedeeler.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Damudge Deeler</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(3/4/02 7:15:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: fOR CLASSES THAT ARE SOMEWHAT RELIANT ON BUFFS-TWO WORDS</span><hr size=1> Surprised that no one told you this:<br><br>INCREASE Magic resistance as much as possible. After all, if you can avoid their spells, your chance fo surviving goes WAY up.  <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=19594> Magelo Profile </a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugielgiel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Giel Giel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(3/5/02 6:01:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: fOR CLASSES THAT ARE SOMEWHAT RELIANT ON BUFFS-TWO WORDS</span><hr size=1> 30 secs to buff then fight is no time at all, you'll maybe get like 3 buffs off during that time and remem your offensive spells.  So if you have 3 buffs and everyone else has about the same...you are screwed.  The pet classes are gonna call up pets, the warrior is gonna shred through all of u.  <br><br>buffs I would do are SoW (u didnt' mention jboots), Regen, Skin, Resist magic if u have time.  After that Dot em all with Drifting death and run around alot.  AFter buffing up you probably will be at like 4 bubs of mana, so the idea here is to last the longest...the pet classes imo are gonna own u though in a close space like that.  and you all better kill the melee first <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uraynebowgodess.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RaynebowGodess</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(3/30/02 12:34:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: fOR CLASSES THAT ARE SOMEWHAT RELIANT ON BUFFS-TWO WORDS</span><hr size=1> imho (assuming it's an all out brawl [anything goes]) drop a line to the warrior before the start and mention the power of the necro with there almost mage like powerful pet and ability to fear <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>step two...screw buffs, hit urself with DS then med back to full (prey the shaman buffs fully) and the mage will prolly hit himself with buffs so since everyone will be at 70-80 mana to start the rumble and your at 100% u have an advantage!<br><br>watch the mage!  keep your eye on the mage! once his pet is on someone (hopefully not you)  nuke the pee water out of him.  this will bring his HP LOOOW  mages at that level only have about 1k hp, if uhit them with starfire its gonna HURT.<br><br>proceed to a necro do same thing...(pretend ur quad kiting) <br><br>the goal isnt to kill everyone one at a time, but to soften them up as much as possible!<br><br>the warrior will prolly be finishing up what u leave undone. a caster at half health should take him all of 20 seconds each.<br><br>(yes i am talking about beefing up your chances at anothers expense but it works)<br><br>ok so now IF u dont have everyone on you (shouldnt have if u do it sneaky enough...)  run behind a pillar and hide...med...repeat....(u did work your hide skill i hope it is a fab advantage pvp specially under those rules)<br><br>pray the necro doesnt dmf as a buff...if not the chances of anyone having see invis on board are slim to none.<br><br>star fire has a huge range u can cast from far enough away that they dont see u casting, soon as it is off the cuff HIDE.<br><br>why do i not say dot?  casters dispell, tanks use stones, why waste mana??  and with sufficeint wisdom u can cast this lovely six hundred 12 point nuke at LEAST 10 times.<br><br>druids may not have the biggest nukes in the game, but ours are very mana efficeint for the damage/mana ratio.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showPrevMessage?topicID=13.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showNextMessage?topicID=13.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.execpc.com/~msippel/thedruidsgrove/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.emailToFriend?topicID=13.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.threadControl?topicID=13.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=13.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=13.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thedruidsgrovegeneral">General - EQ<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm27">General - DAOC<option value="thedruidsgrovegeneralot">General - OT<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm29">The Druids Circle<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm18">FAQ & Index<option value="thedruidsgrov